  "prompt": "I am a Canadian student in grade 11, and want a summer job over seas. What should I do?",
  "response": "Here are several options for a Canadian student seeking a summer job overseas:\n\n1. Work Exchange Programs\n- SWAP Working Holidays\n- International Experience Canada (IEC)\n- BUNAC Programs\n\n2. Teaching English Abroad\n- TEFL/TESOL certification\n- Programs in:\n- South Korea\n- Japan\n- China\n- Vietnam\n\n3. International Internships\n- Through universities\n- Websites like AIESEC\n- Internships in:\n- Europe\n- Asia\n- Australia\n\n4. Volunteer Opportunities\n- Projects Abroad\n- YMCA International\n- Volunteer programs in:\n- Africa\n- South America\n- Asia\n\n5. Specific Job Search Platforms\n- Indeed International\n- Global Job Search Websites\n- WorkAway\n- CoolWorks\n\nRecommended Preparation:\n- Valid passport\n- Travel insurance\n- Basic language skills\n- Research visa requirements\n- Save money for initial expenses\n- Get parental/guardian consent\n- Check government travel advisories\n\nConsiderations:\n- Budget carefully\n- Understand work permits\n- Check age restrictions\n- Ensure program legitimacy\n- Consider safety and health precautions\n\nConsult your school's career counselor for personalized guidance.",
